{
  "documentMetadata": {
    "title": "Sinusitis, Acute, Failure of Empiric Therapy",
    "sourceFile": "Sinusitis, Acute, Failure of Empiric Therapy.pdf",
    "lastUpdated": "2025-04-22"
  },
  "content": [
    {
      "type": "header",
      "level": 1,
      "text": "Clinical Setting"
    },
    {
      "type": "nestedContent",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "Acute sinusitis, clinical failure after 3 days of empiric antibacterial treatment:"
        },
        {
          "type": "list",
          "items": [
            "Persistent sinus pain, nasal congestion, purulent nasal discharge and, perhaps, fever despite recommended therapy."
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "nestedContent",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "Could result from:"
        },
        {
          "type": "list",
          "items": [
            "Infection due to an antibiotic resistant organism",
            "Obstruction of the ostium of one or more sinuses",
            "Rarely, deep fungal infection (especially if immunocompromised patient or insulin-dependent diabetic",
            "Sinusitis due to a non-infectious disease; e.g., Granulomatosis with polyangiitis (Formerly Wegener's granulomatosis)"
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "list",
      "items": [
        "Optional diagnostic method: collection of sinus exudate for culture by either sinus puncture or direct sinus endoscopy.",
        "For initial empiric therapy of acute sinusitis, see Sinusitis, Acute, Empiric Therapy."
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "header",
      "level": 1,
      "text": "Etiologies"
    },
    {
      "type": "list",
      "items": [
        "Strep. pneumoniae (33%)",
        "H. influenzae (32%)",
        "M. catarrhalis (9%)",
        "Streptococcus sp. (Group A) (2%)",
        "Anaerobes (6%)",
        "Viral (15%)",
        "Staph. aureus"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "list",
      "items": [
        "See Clin Infect Dis 54:826, 2012; Clin Infect Dis 45:e121, 2007: Data analysis suggests S. aureus should NOT be considered a potential etiology of acute uncomplicated sinusitis; incidence of positive cultures same as the incidence in asymptomatic controls. Hence, positive culture may represent only colonization."
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "header",
      "level": 1,
      "text": "Primary Regimens"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "Empiric Therapy Failure Adjustment"
    },
    {
      "type": "nestedContent",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "Child: Empiric second line recommendations in the absence of cultures:"
        },
        {
          "type": "drugRegimen",
          "regimenData": {
            "intent": "treatment",
            "condition": "For children failing Amoxicillin",
            "components": [
              {
                "drug": "Amoxicillin-clavulanate (extra strength) suspension",
                "dose": "90 mg/kg/day (Amox component)",
                "route": "po",
                "frequency": "divided q12h"
              }
            ],
            "durationDetail": {
              "fixedDuration": "10-14 days"
            }
          }
        },
        {
          "type": "drugRegimen",
          "regimenData": {
            "intent": "treatment",
            "condition": "For children failing Amoxicillin-clavulanate",
            "components": [
              {
                "drug": "Clindamycin",
                "dose": "30-40 mg/kg/day",
                "frequency": "divided q8h",
                "connector": "+"
              },
              {
                "drug": "Cefuroxime axetil",
                "dose": "30 mg/kg/day",
                "route": "po",
                "frequency": "divided q12h",
                "connector": "or"
              },
              {
                "drug": "Cefdinir",
                "dose": "14 mg/kg/day",
                "frequency": "divided q12h or q24h",
                "connector": "or"
              },
              {
                "drug": "Cefpodoxime",
                "dose": "10 mg/kg/day",
                "route": "po",
                "frequency": "divided q12h"
              }
            ],
            "notes": "Note: Cefuroxime susp not available in the US, may be available in other markets."
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "nestedContent",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "Adult: If failure to respond, empiric therapy pending culture results;"
        },
        {
          "type": "drugRegimen",
          "regimenData": {
            "intent": "treatment",
            "condition": "If mild (outpatient)",
            "components": [
              {
                "drug": "Amoxicillin-clavulanate",
                "dose": "1000mg/62.5 mg tabs; Tabs 2",
                "route": "po",
                "frequency": "bid",
                "connector": "or"
              },
              {
                "drug": "Levofloxacin",
                "dose": "750 mg",
                "route": "po",
                "frequency": "once daily"
              }
            ]
          }
        },
        {
          "type": "drugRegimen",
          "regimenData": {
            "intent": "treatment",
            "condition": "If severe (inpatient)",
            "components": [
              {
                "drug": "Ceftriaxone",
                "dose": "1-2 gm",
                "route": "IV",
                "frequency": "q24 h",
                "connector": "or"
              },
              {
                "drug": "Ampicillin-sulbactam",
                "dose": "3 gm",
                "route": "IV",
                "frequency": "q6h",
                "connector": "or"
              },
              {
                "drug": "Levofloxacin",
                "dose": "750 mg",
                "route": "IV/po",
                "frequency": "q24h"
              }
            ]
          }
        },
        {
          "type": "list",
          "items": [
            "If no response within 24 hrs, CT scan of sinuses and surgical consultation"
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "header",
      "level": 1,
      "text": "Alternative Regimens"
    },
    {
      "type": "nestedContent",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "Directed/Specific Therapy"
        },
        {
          "type": "list",
          "items": [
            "Base choice of agent on results of culture and susceptibility testing"
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "header",
      "level": 1,
      "text": "Comments"
    },
    {
      "type": "list",
      "items": [
        "See IDSA Clinical Practice Guidelines, Clin Infect Dis 54:e72, 2012; AAP Guidelines for Children: Pediatrics Jun 24, 2013.",
        "Acute sinusitis in adults: N Engl J Med. 2016;375(10):962-970. doi:10.1056/NEJMcp1601749"
      ]
    }
  ]
}